'''Yaimar Abel Medina Ortiz''' (born 5 November 2004) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a midfielder for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
Medina came through the academy at [[Independiente del Valle]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/39364103/young-stars-shine-conmebol-olympic-qualifying-kicks-off |website=ESPN|title= Young stars shine as CONMEBOL Olympic qualifying kicks off|first=Tim|last=Vickery|accessdate=24 January 2024|date=23 January 2024}}</ref> He made his debut in the first team on 30 July 2022 against [[Barcelona S.C.]] in [[Ecuadorian Serie A]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://el.soccerway.com/matches/2022/07/31/ecuador/primera-a/independiente-jose-teran/barcelona-sporting-club-guayaquil/3735194/|date=30 July 2022|accessdate=24 January 2024|title= INDEPENDIENTE VALLE VS. BARCELONA 1 - 1|website=Soccerway}}</ref> He scored his first league goal on 2 June 2023 in Serie A, contributing to his team's 2–0 victory over [[S.D. Aucas]].<ref>{{cite web|website=ESPN|accessdate=24 January 2024|url= https://www.espn.com.ec/futbol/ecuador/nota/_/id/12143330/independiente-del-valle-vencio-a-aucas-y-casi-gana-la-etapa|title= Independiente del Valle won and puts the stage in its pocket|date=2 June 2023}}</ref>

On 9 January 2025, Medina signed a 4.5-year contract with [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in Belgium.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Genk|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/en/news/5800/ecuadorian-international-yaimar-medina-20-signs-with-krc-genk|title=Ecuadorian international Yaimar Medina (20) signs with KRC Genk|date=9 January 2025|access-date=10 January 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
He was part of the [[Ecuador national under-20 football team]] that took part in the [[2023 South American U-20 Championship]] in Colombia, in which his Ecuador side achieved fourth place, ensuring its qualification for the 2023 U-20 World Cup held in Argentina.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bola.net/piala_dunia/profil-tim-dan-daftar-pemain-ekuador-di-piala-dunia-u-20-2023-eaeac4.html|website=Bola.net|accessdate=24 January 2024|title= Team Profile and List of Ecuador Players in the 2023 U-20 World Cup|first=Serafin Unus|last=Pasi |date=March 24, 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37636311/brazil-south-american-u20-champions|website=ESPN|accessdate=24 January 2024|title= Brazil are South American U20 champions, but real winners will be known in a decade|first=Tim|last=Vickery|date=13 February 2023}}</ref>

On 27 December 2023, he was included by coach Miguel Bravo in the [[Ecuador national under-23 football team]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://studiofutbol.com.ec/2023/12/27/oficial-convocados-de-ecuador-para-el-preolimpico-2024/|website=Studio Futbol|accessdate=24 January 2024|title= OFFICIAL: Called from Ecuador for the 2024 Pre-Olympic|first=Brian|last=Campoverde|date=December 27, 2023}}</ref> On his debut, he scored two goals against Colombia U23. He also scored again in his second match against Venezuela U20.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.primicias.ec/noticias/jugada/ecuador-goleada-colombia-preolimpico/|website=Primicias.ec|accessdate=24 January 2024|title=Scoring debut! Ecuador beats Colombia in the Pre-Olympic|first=Felipe|last=Larrea|date=20 January 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/la-tri/video-gol-yaimar-medina-ecuador-venezuela_0_a648dSSb57.html|website=Ole.com|accessdate=24 January 2024|title= Video: Yaimar Medina's great free kick goal against Venezuela|date=23 January 2024 }}</ref>

Medina made his debut for the senior [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]] on 6 September 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against Brazil at the [[Estádio Couto Pereira]]. He substituted [[Pervis Estupiñán]] in the 85th minute, Brazil won 1–0.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/684610/ecuador-brazil|title=Brazil v Ecuador game report|date=6 September 2024}}</ref>

